<sect1 id="composer">
<title>Composing Your Mail</title>


 <sect2 id="composer-window">
 <title>Composer Window</title>   
    <sect3 id="compose-message">
    <title>Compose</title>
    <subtitle>Write that letter</subtitle>
    <para>&key; Ctrl + N</para>
    <para>After selecting the Compose  function you are presented with the <link linkend="composer-icons">Mail Compose Window </link>( Dialog.)
    </para>
    <para>There are three primary areas and a few different functions available from this dialog.
    </para>
    <para>1. 
    <link linkend="composer-icons">The Top Icon Bar</link> See  <xref linkend="composer-icons"> for more information.
    </para>
    <para>2. 
      <link linkend="address-entry-fields">The Address Entry Fields</link> See <xref linkend="address-entry-fields"> below for more information.
    </para>
    <para>3. 
    <link linkend="text-entry-message"> The Message Entry or Edit Window.</link> See <xref linkend="text-entry-message">below for more information.
    </para>
    
             
    <sect4 id="account-message">
    <title>Select Account</title>
    <para>By default the first account you configured is pre-loaded into this field</para>
    <para>To choose another account select the arrow
     on the right hand side of this field and click the account name you require</para>
      </sect4>
      
     <sect4 id="address-entry-fields">
      <title>Receivers Address</title>
      <para>These three fields (TO, CC and BCC) are the places you enter the full E-mail address of the person(s)
      to whom you are writing.</para>
       <itemizedlist>
       <listitem>
       <para>TO</para>
       <para>The primary person or group your mail is directed to</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
       <para>CC</para>
       <para> Send a Carbon Copy to this person</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
       <para>BCC</para>
       <para> Send a<quote> Blind Carbon Copy</quote>.</para>
       </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
      </sect4>
       
       <sect4 id="subject-message">
       <title>Mail Subject</title>
       <para>Write a short, clear heading for your mail here</para>
       </sect4>
       
      <sect4 id="text-entry-message">
   <title>The Mail Body</title>
    <subtitle>The letter / message itself</subtitle>
    <para>This is what it is all about . 
    The primary reason for having a mail application at all.</para>
    <para> Here you type in your pearls of prose .</para>
    <para>Please note that basic cut and paste is supported as is including the contents of a file.
     If you want to be sure that your recipient can read your stuff the safest choice would be plain text but theoretically
      anything that may be presented as text may be pasted into here.</para>
     </sect4>
     
    </sect3>
